     By the way Saturne, I see you mention noone quite often!  Who is he? <p></p><span class=m><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bbbarden.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chanelco>Chanelco</A> at: 10/14/02 5:43:48 am<br></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=34.topic&index=35><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bbbarden.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raerenee>RaeRenee</A> </span><br><BR><img src=http://www.poingenterprises.com/gothhenge/rae/raepretty60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60><br> <span class=usertitle>Frozen Rock<br /><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-1-5.gif /></span><br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 10/14/02 5:54:24 am</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> Re: -</span><hr size=1> Sorus, excellent post.  I haven't got much to add to it, save that there is a LARGE amount of Americans who DO NOT want us to go to war, and who disapprove of Bush's actions.  While everyone's going on about how no one will stop him and no one speaks up, I don't think they've heard anything about the anti-war rallies that have been held.<br>
<br>
If you ask me, this is all a political agenda to get him re-elected.  When W came into office, it was through unscrupulous means, and the whole country knew it.  It's been documented and proven, but when Sept 11th hit, we all held our breath and supported him because he weas our &quot;Fearless&quot; leader...  The kind of father figure kids want to grow up with, saying the people who did this are &quot;evil&quot; and that we're gonna get them.<br>
<br>
So our boys went over and kicked some Taliban butt.  Why we're suddenly concerned with Saddam again is beyond me.  Why Bush feels compelled to take the divine right of judgement and call Saddam an &quot;Evil&quot; man, is beyond me.  All I know is that approval ratings for a president go up when a country is at war, and he wants to get re-elected.  I mean, he's got about 2 years, and that's when the primaries hit.  <br>
<br>
People aren't buying it over here altogether either.  We know our country's past.  We know that W's daddy helped Saddam gain power to keep Iran off our backs in the 80s.  We know that the Reagan administration gave them the money and the strains of the viruses necessary to put together a bioterrorist threat.   What I don't understand is why, after a long war, where we didn't even get the bad guy (Totally angered me and others) we are changing our focus to someone who we let live when the country already did hate him...   I mean with South Park, he's almost become a laughable character to us. (Don't get me wrong, but I'd bet you more Americans have watched the South Park movie than have done their political homework.)<br>
<br>
I don't believe this will be WW3.  I don't believe Bush will get the backing from his own people that he would need to make the war a success, let alone the help from European countries.  And, even if he DID get the backing, I doubt there would be sufficient backing for Iraq to truly make it into a World War.<br>
<br>
The sad truth about this whole situation is that you cannot fight an abstract.  You cannot fight terrorism anymore than you can fight creativity or immaturity.  Life is not a movie.  When you kill the bad guy, it's not a happy ending.  It doesn't make everything better..  It's just a symptom of a larger problem. <br>
<br>
Killing more people won't make terrorism go away, or make what happened last year any less painful.  <br>
<br>
The way I see it is this - if America, Afghanistan, and Iraq were just people, it'd be like a school yard fight... it'd be like the Al Queda network in Afghanistan punched America in the gut.  Then we beat the ever-lovin shit out of Afghanistan, and since we didn't feel like the job was done, we're going after someone we think is Al Queda's friend who we can beat on next, just to prove we're stronger.  It's not solving anything.  *sigh* <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=34.topic&index=36><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2 bgcolor=#FFFFFF><table cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td align=right class=headings> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=34.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"></a>  <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=34.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"></a>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.emailToFriend?topicID=34.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/email.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="email this topic to a friend"></a> </td></tr></table></td></tr></table></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bbbarden>bbarden network</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57>Debates</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.bbarden.com">bbarden network</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <br />

